Good question. I would also like to understand how many people actually work on data labeling. I suppose any potential customer of data labeling will ask the same question. But now it is impossible to find out and count. There are about 240 miners in the subnet. In theory, at least 3 people should work per miner per day. In total, there should be about 720 working data labelers during the day. But at one time, for example, 240 people can work in the network (one person per miner). But this has not been proven.
